item.description:
Ever wanted to parse /etc/oratab but ignore all the comments and blank lines? So did I. Here&rsquo;s how &hellip;
I can&rsquo;t claim all the credit for this, it is based on something I was doing plus a bit of &ldquo;stolen&rdquo; code from SLES.
1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 9 OLDIFS=$IFS IFS=: grep -v &#39;^\(#\|$\)&#39; /etc/oratab |\ while read ORASID ORAHOME AUTOSTART do ## Do what you like here with ## $ORASID, $ORAHOME and $AUTOSTART ## done IFS=$OLDIFS Cheers,
